title: For Sale:  New Colt M4 6921 Upper Complete with extras 14.5"
location: Goose Creek Moncks Corner Summerville, Charleston, South Carolina
postcontent:
Brand new Colt M4 flat top upper with 14.5" Barrel. A great upper for your pistol build, SBR or you can pin and weld the flash hider to bring it to the legal length.   Also an outstanding upper if you have a full auto lower, the buffer in this package reduces your rate of fire to a much more controllable rate for tighter/shorter groups.  

Included in this sale are:

The complete upper receiver assembly with Bolt Carrier Group and charging handle.

Knight's armament rail system with various panels that you can customize with

Matech Backup iron sight, adjustable for both windage and elevation, also new

Removable carryhandle sight, slightly used, but in perfect working order.

H6 carbine Buffer (5.3 oz) this buffer is very heavy and greatly reduces the felt recoil and also aids in fast recovery/re-aquisiton of your target.  In other words, faster follow up time between rounds.  This is what the Marine Corps is going to.  

Prefer local sale, but will ship to lower 48, add $18.00 to the price.   Cash or US postal money orders only, no exceptions.

No trades at this time, got another project I'm working on.
This is a package deal, would prefer to keep it all together, and it's a great deal considering you are saving a couple hundred bucks.

Price is firm and very fair.   Please call or text, I'm not around the computer much and my emails are slow getting to my so called "Smart Phone".   843 670 96three six

If you are unsure of the legalities of owning a 14.5" upper, you can research it on the BATFE website.  But in short, you cannot legally buy this and install it on a rifle lower receiver in the condition it is in.  The flash hider or an even longer one would need to be pinned and welded according to the BATFE guidelines to bring the barrel to 16" or longer before you can install on your lower.  There are many flash hiders and compensators on the market that fit the need and some will enhance the performance of the weapon system once completed.  My experience with this barrel length shows me that the accuracy is darn good out to about 400m, beyond that, I use a rifle length upper.  I personally run the FSC556 Compensator/brake and the H6 buffer combined to achieve an "almost none" recoil.   Ammo is too expensive to waste missing your target.  


Check out my other quality items for sale. (link at the top of the page)  Thanks for looking and taking the time to read my long winded ad.

title: For Sale:  CAREER II 707 Cal 5.5 or .22
postcontent:
Selling My Air Rifle CAREER II 707 Very Hard to find,Like Brand New! With  " Simmons 1048 M1 "Scope
Price $399 will take some trade's let me know what you got...

The Career 707 blew the doors off the PCP market when it was introduced in the US in the 1990s. Even after all these years, this airgun continues to be a favorite among hunters.

The variable power levels give you a huge range of energy for taking small- and medium-sized game at distances previously reserved only for firearms. The gun is manufactured by ShinSung, a Korean company that knows what hunters need and want, because Koreans have been using the Career far longer to hunt all types of game.

The Monte Carlo Indonesian hardwood stock has a raised cheekpiece and checkering on the wrist (directly above the lever). The forearm also has checkering to ensure a firm grip when you're in the thick of things. The lever-action cocking mechanism works quickly, smoothly and effortlessly as you chamber each pellet from the multi-shot magazine.

The number of shots you can load in the mag depends on the length of the pellets, but most people load about 6 pellets (although you can fit 10 Crosman Premiers!). Longer ones take up more room, so you won't be able to load as many. 

The built-in manometer (air pressure gauge) shows you how much air remains in the two built-in air reservoirs, located directly below the barrel. This air rifle was the first to offer adjustable velocities with its integral power wheel. Adjust the wheel to accommodate heavy or light pellets, long or short distances and the type of game you're shooting. The gun adjusts to YOUR needs instead of the other way around! Max velocity is 1,250 fps in .22 cal. and 1,000 fps in .25 cal. You'll get up to 20 full-power shots.

The two-stage trigger can be adjusted to your shooting preference. The front sight is a hunting-style ramp with a bead, and the rear sight is fully adjustable. The Career 707 is known for its accuracy.
